[line]
[size=4][b]What Is Huginn?[/b][/size]

Huginn watches what your character can see and feel — your health dropping, the dragon overhead, the forge in front of you — and surfaces the most useful items in a set of hotkey slots. No menu diving. No pausing to swap spells. Just glance and press.

It only uses information your character already has or what the player can observe. This is a convenience tool, not a cheat tool.


[line]
[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://skse.silverlock.org/]SKSE64[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/32444]Address Library for SKSE Plugins[/url]
[/list]
[size=3][b]Optional: Wheeler Integration[/b][/size]

A wheeler integration was made to allow for a more game-pad native UI/UX experience. For this, you have two options:
 
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/167380]wheelerAPI[/url] — Radial menu integration (LandingCrew Fork) with v2 API support. This is included as an optional download in the FOMOD or as a standalone mod. You need the assets from [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/97345]WheelerAPI - Wheeler - Quick Action Wheel Of Skyrim[/url] as a prerequisite and allow Huggin's wheelerAPI dll to overwrite it. (install wheeler before you install huggin)
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/167380]WHEELER - Refined[/url] — Radial menu integration with v1 API support. Installation order should not matte
[/list]Some features: 
[list]
[*]Each Huginn page becomes a managed Wheeler wheel
[*]Auto-focuses the Huginn wheel when Wheeler opens (configurable)
[*]Auto-navigates to Huginn wheel on urgent overrides
[*]Subtext labels: wildcard picks, override alerts, context explanations (v2 API)
[*]Post-activation behavior: backfill with next candidate, stay sticky, or clear
[*]Equipping via Wheeler triggers Huginn's learning system
[/list]
API Differences: [list]
[*]V1 Includes all core functionality and error handling
[*]V2 extends V1 with optional features such as huggin controlled UI elements
[/list]

[size=3][b][size=3][b]Optional: [/b][/size] dMenu Integration[/b][/size]

[b]Optional.[/b] Provides an in-game settings panel for Huginn — toggle the widget, adjust position/opacity/scale, remap keybinds, reset learning data — all without touching an INI file.

[line]

[size=4][b]How It Works[/b][/size]

During normal gameplay, Huginn:
[list=1]
[*]Reads your situation — vitals, buffs, enemies, environment
[*]Scores every relevant item in your inventory against that context
[*]Fills your slots with the highest-utility picks
[*]Displays them on a HUD widget and/or a Wheeler radial wheel
[/list]
You press a hotkey(or select the wheeler slot). The item is equips/used. Huginn notices what you chose and learns for next time.

[line]

[size=4][b]Features[/b][/size]

[size=3][b]Context-Aware Recommendations[/b][/size]

Huginn reads 11 independent sensor streams to understand what's happening:

[list]
[*][b]Player Vitals[/b] — Health, Magicka, and Stamina tracked as continuous values with urgency detection. Depletion rate tracking catches sustained damage patterns like bleed effects.
[*][b]Status Effects[/b] — On fire? Poisoned? Frost/shock DoT? Diseased? Huginn knows, and resist potions/spells rise to the top.
[*][b]Active Buffs[/b] — Already have Invisibility? An armor spell? A summon out? Huginn won't waste a slot suggesting what you already have.
[*][b]Resistances[/b] — High fire resist means fire resist potions drop in priority. Low poison resist near Falmer? Resist Poison climbs.
[*][b]Equipment State[/b] — Melee, ranged, staff, shield, dual-wield, enchanted weapon charge — all tracked. Low on charge? Soul gems appear.
[*][b]Enemies[/b] — Up to 50 enemies tracked. Type classified (Humanoid, Undead, Beast, Dragon, Construct, Daedra). Distance, count, and whether they're casting spells — all factor in.
[*][b]Environment[/b] — At a forge? Looking at a locked door? Standing at an alchemy lab? The right tool for the job appears.
[*][b]Survival Mode[/b] — Full CC Survival Mode and SurvivalModeImproved support. Hunger, cold, and fatigue tracked.
[*][b]Movement & Position[/b] — Sneaking, mounted, overencumbered.
[/list]
Each Sensor triggers relevant updates to provide time relevant suggestions.

[size=3][b]What Gets Surfaced When[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Health dropping ﻿→ Healing spells and potions rise sharply
[*]On fire ﻿→ Resist Fire items get 8x priority
[*]Looking at a lock ﻿→ Unlock spells appear
[*]At a forge ﻿→ Fortify Smithing potions appear
[*]Enemy casting spells → Wards rise in priority
[*]Multiple enemies → AoE spells climb
[*]Undead targets → Turn Undead and Sun damage surface
[*]Sneaking ﻿→ Invisibility and Muffle become relevant
[*]Enchanted weapon empty ﻿→ Soul gems appear at 9x priority
[*]Bow equipped, low arrows ﻿→ Ammo surfaces
[/list]
[size=3][b]Urgency Overrides[/b][/size]

When things get critical, Huginn cuts through normal scoring and forces the most important items into your top slots:

[list]
[*][b]Critical Health[/b] (HP < 35%) — Healing items forced to top priority
[*][b]Critical Magicka[/b] (MP < 35%) — Magicka restore forced up
[*][b]Critical Stamina[/b] (SP < 35%) — Stamina restore forced up
[*][b]Low Ammo[/b] — arrows/bolts surfaced
[*][b]Weapon Empty[/b] — Soul gems when enchanted weapon hits 0% charge
[/list]
All thresholds configurable. Hysteresis prevents flickering (e.g., health override activates at 35%, deactivates at 50%).

[line]

[size=3][b]Learns Your Preferences[/b][/size]

Huginn uses lightweight reinforcement learning to adapt to how [i]you[/i] play.

[list]
[*][b]Equip via Huginn hotkey[/b] → Strong positive signal. "I wanted this item in this situation."
[*][b]Equip via vanilla menu[/b] → Weaker signal. "The player chose this, but maybe not because of Huginn."
[*][b]Add favorites →  [/b]Sends passive boost to Huginn, I like this, show me more for this.[b][/b]
[*][b]Quick-switch away[/b] (equip then immediately swap within 3 seconds) → Negative signal. "That was a misclick."
[*][b]Items unused for a long time[/b] → Gradual preference decay. Old habits fade.
[/list]
Learning persists across save/load via SKSE cosave. Each character has independent preferences.

New items start with minimal learning influence. After ~5 uses, Huginn has a decent read on your preference. After ~15, it's confident.

[size=3][b]Wildcard Exploration[/b][/size]

Optionally, lower-priority slots will occasionally show items you haven't tried yet — giving the learner a chance to discover that you actually love that Scroll of Blizzard you forgot about. Configurable probability, cooldown, and which slots participate.

[line]

[size=3][b]Item Support[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Spells[/b] — Every spell the player knows. Auto-classified by school, damage type, role (healing, damage, buff, summon, utility, defensive). Optionally filters uncastable spells.
[*][b]Potions & Consumables[/b] — Health, Magicka, Stamina restores. Resist potions. Buff potions. Cure Disease/Poison. Poisons (damage, paralyze, slow, fear, frenzy). -Work in progress/Needs validation   ﻿
[*][b]Food & Drink[/b] — Survival Mode food with hunger/cold satisfaction. Alcohol auto-detected (ale, mead, wine, skooma, and more — plus keyword detection for CACO and other overhauls). -Work in progress/Needs validation   
[*][b]Weapons[/b] — Favorited weapons, classified by type. Enchanted weapon charge tracked. Silver weapons get bonus vs. undead.
[*][b]Ammo[/b] — Arrows and bolts, matched to equipped bow/crossbow.
[*][b]Scrolls[/b] — Classified using the same system as spells.
[*][b]Soul Gems[/b] — Filled gems surfaced when enchanted weapons need recharging.
[/list]

[line]

[size=3][b]Multi-Page Slot System[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Up to 10 pages, each with up to 10 slots
[*]Each slot has a classification — restrict it to damage spells, healing items, potions, weapons, food, or leave it open
[*]Slots have configurable [b]priority[/b] (higher-priority slots get filled first), [b]wildcard[/b] toggle, and [b]override routing[/b] (e.g., "this slot only receives health emergencies")
[/list][list]
[*]Slot locking prevents recommendations from flickering when context changes briefly
[/list][list]
[*]Page cycling via hotkey (default [font=Courier New]-[/font] and [font=Courier New]=[/font])
[/list]
[b]Pre-made templates included:[/b]
[list]
[*]Battlemage — Destruction + melee + emergency healing
[*]Paladin — Restoration-focused combat
[*]Pure Mage — All schools, prioritizing spells
[*]Stealth Archer — Ranged focus with poison and utility
[*]Summoner — Conjuration-heavy with summon management
[*]Survivalist — Survival Mode oriented with food and utility
[/list]

[line]

[size=3][b]HUD Widget[/b][/size]

A lightweight Scaleform overlay on your HUD showing current slot recommendations.

[list]
[*][b]Three display modes:[/b] Minimal (name only), Normal (name + context details), Verbose (full score breakdown)
[*][b]Animations:[/b] Slide, fade, or instant transitions. Urgent override slots pulse. Confirm dip on re-evaluation.
[*][b]Fully repositionable[/b] — screen percentage coordinates, works at any resolution/aspect ratio
[*][b]Adjustable[/b] opacity and scale (separate child element opacity for page labels and dots)
[*][b]Auto-hides[/b] in menus — inventory, map, crafting, dialogue, barter, lockpicking. Stays visible during console and favorites.
[*][b]Persists through loading screens[/b] — automatically re-shows after cell transitions
[*][b]Dynamic background width[/b] — panel auto-sizes to fit long item names
[*][b]Page indicator[/b] — active page dot shows an inline label (e.g., "Smart", "Inventory")
[*]Can be disabled entirely if you prefer Wheeler-only
[/list]
[size=3][b]Keybindings[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Single-Tap[/b] a slot key → Equip to right hand
[*][b]Double-tap[/b] → Equip to left hand
[*][b]Hold[/b] → Equip to both hands
[*]All keys fully remappable via INI or dMenu
[/list]

[line]

[size=3][b]Console Commands[/b][/size]

Open the console ([font=Courier New]~[/font]) and type [font=Courier New]hg[/font]:

[list]
[*][font=Courier New]hg refresh[/font] — Force immediate recommendation update
[*][font=Courier New]hg reload[/font] — Hot-reload all settings from INI (no restart needed)
[*][font=Courier New]hg status[/font] — Show system status
[*][font=Courier New]hg unlock[/font] — Clear all slot locks
[*][font=Courier New]hg rebuild[/font] — Force rebuild all registries
[*][font=Courier New]hg page N[/font] — Switch to page N
[*][font=Courier New]hg weights <FormID>[/font] — Inspect learning weights for an item
[*][font=Courier New]hg reset qvalues[/font] — Clear all learned preferences
[*][font=Courier New]hg reset all[/font] — Full system reset
[/list]

[line]

[size=3][b]Mod Compatibility[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]ENB / ReShade[/b] — No conflicts
[*][b]CC Survival Mode[/b] — Full support (hunger, cold, fatigue)
[*][b]SurvivalModeImproved (SMI)[/b] — Full support
[*][b]Spell overhauls[/b] (Apocalypse, Triumvirate, Mysticism, Odin, Adamant/Vokrii) — Auto-classification works out of the box. Override INI available for edge cases.
[*][b]Potion overhauls[/b] (CACO, Lorerim, Requiem, etc.) — Keyword detection + manual override INI
[*][b]Combat mods[/b] (MCO, Precision, Chocolate Poise, TK Dodge, DMCO) — Compatible
[*][b]ImmersiveHUD SKSE[/b] — Compatible
[*][b]SPID[/b] — Compatible (distributed spells picked up within 5 seconds)
[/list]
[b]Not currently supported:[/b]
[list]
[*]Frostfall, Sunhelm, iNeed — These use different global variables than CC Survival Mode. Cold/hunger/fatigue sensors will not read from these mods. 
[/list]
[b]Requiem / Lorerim note:[/b] Requiem stops magicka regeneration in combat. Huginn's default weights are tuned for vanilla magicka behavior. Requiem/Lorerim users should adjust context weights in the INI for best results (higher restore-magicka potion weight, higher melee fallback threshold).

[line]

[size=3][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

Everything is configurable via [font=Courier New]Data/SKSE/Plugins/Huginn.ini[/font] — scoring parameters, context weights, override thresholds, slot layouts, widget appearance, keybindings, learning behavior, Wheeler settings, and more.

Modded spells and items that aren't auto-classified correctly can be manually overridden in [font=Courier New]Huginn_Overrides.ini[/font] by name or FormID.

All settings hot-reloadable with [font=Courier New]hg reload[/font]. No game restart required.

[line]

[size=3][b]Performance[/b][/size]

Huginn is designed to be low impact and lazy .

[list]
[*][b]Tiered update loop[/b] — Not a flat 100ms hammer. Override checks and UI render run every frame (~1ms). Context polling runs at 100–500ms. The full scoring pipeline only runs when game state has meaningfully changed (dirty-flag + hash comparison).
[*][b]Adaptive timing[/b] — Polling speeds up 2x in combat, slows down 2x during long idle. Configurable.
[*][b]Pipeline skips entirely[/b] when nothing has changed — no wasted cycles.
[*][b]Q-learning updates are async[/b] — queued and processed without blocking the game thread.
[*][b]Slot locks prevent churn[/b] — recommendations hold stable, reducing unnecessary UI updates.
[/list]
During profiling and testing with Tracy, max memory usage was

[line]

[size=3][b]Known Limitations (Alpha)[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Soul gems display correctly on the HUD widget and recharge works via hotkey, but [b]appear as empty circles in Wheeler wheels[/b] (Skyrim engine limitation — Wheeler cannot display soul gem forms). Togglable via INI.
[*]Widget may show during some "cutscenes".
[*]Widget is not compatible with 
[*]Survival mode hunger/cold/fatigue sensors may report inaccurate values in some configurations (calibration in progress).
[*]Modded spells the classifier can't categorize (type "Unknown") are currently excluded from recommendations. Override INI can fix specific spells.
[*]Changing mod load order between sessions may orphan Q-learning data for removed/replaced mods (learning for remaining mods is unaffected).
[/list]
